<meta title="V3ctor">

<md>
    Math is one of these things people seem to hate, but it is one of my favourite parts
    of programming.

    I usually solve the problems on the go - as you do - but it would be nice to save some
    generic solutions for later. And this is where V3ctor comes in.

    V3ctor is a generic math library that allows you to fluently solve geometric
    problems.
    ```cs
    var points = Parabola.With( a: -1, c: 0 ).SolveB.WhereTipY( 10 ).Intersect( Line.From( -10, 10 ).Through( 0, 0 ) );
    ```
    V3ctor is fully struct based, so heap allocations that reduce performance are non-existant.
</md>
