    Given just how many non-trivial operations exist, V3ctor is constantly growing.
    In the case of intersection and closest points it is possible to [brute-force](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brute-force_attack)
    a given domain in most cases, but that is obviously not optimal, and as such
    I am constantly adding more and more math solutions to it.

    You might not believe me, but [Desmos](https://www.desmos.com/calculator) - pictured above - is a really usefull tool.
